Subject: [build] add napi_v8_disable_whole_program_vtables knob

V8 standalone + ThinLTO + -fwhole-program-vtables drops vtables for some
classes (torque parser AST nodes, SimpleStringResource<T>) while keeping
their typeinfo, causing `undefined symbol: vtable for ...` at link time on
macOS/iOS, and similar fallout via PartitionAlloc wrap when paired with
is_official_build=true. Upstream report (v8-users 2024 thread "V8
optimized build fails on linking mksnapshot unless thin lto is disabled")
has no fix.

Introduce a build arg defaulting to false (no behavior change for
upstream) so napi-impl can flip it on to keep use_thin_lto=true for size
while skipping the whole-program-vtables sub-optimization.

---
 build/config/compiler/BUILD.gn | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/build/config/compiler/BUILD.gn b/build/config/compiler/BUILD.gn
--- a/build/config/compiler/BUILD.gn
+++ b/build/config/compiler/BUILD.gn
@@ -203,6 +203,16 @@ declare_args() {
   is_wexit_time_destructors_default = true
 }

+declare_args() {
+  # napi-impl: skip `-fwhole-program-vtables` even when use_thin_lto=true.
+  # ThinLTO + whole-program-vtables in V8 standalone drops vtables for some
+  # classes (torque AST nodes, SimpleStringResource<T>) while preserving
+  # typeinfo, causing "undefined symbol: vtable for ..." at link time.
+  # See v8-users 2024 thread
+  # "V8 optimized build fails on linking mksnapshot unless thin lto is disabled".
+  napi_v8_disable_whole_program_vtables = false
+}
+
 declare_args() {
   # Set to true to use icf, Identical Code Folding.
   use_icf = (is_posix || is_fuchsia) && !is_debug && !using_sanitizer &&
@@ -923,7 +933,8 @@ config("compiler") {

     # TODO(crbug.com/40182783): investigate why this isn't effective on
     # arm32.
-    if (!is_android || current_cpu == "arm64") {
+    if ((!is_android || current_cpu == "arm64") &&
+        !napi_v8_disable_whole_program_vtables) {
       cflags += [ "-fwhole-program-vtables" ]

       if (toolchain_supports_rust_thin_lto) {
